children.subject:
I don't think the course has been taught before, it was going to be offered last year but got cancelled. You could email Professor Garg to ask for more details about the course.

At that time last year, I emailed him and got this response (I was also asking whether math 113 is required): 
"The focus of the class will be formal definitions and complexity style constructions. No, abstract algebra is not a prerequisite. Use of group theory would be minimal."
